  10. BUILD & DEPLOYMENT READINESS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SCORE: 8/10

Strengths:
  ✓ Build succeeds cleanly: 0 errors, 0 warnings.
  ✓ All 6 routes statically prerendered:
      / (home), /_not-found, /robots.txt, /sitemap.xml
  ✓ robots.ts generates correct rules (allow all, sitemap URL).
  ✓ sitemap.ts generates a valid sitemap entry for the home URL.
  ✓ JSON-LD structured data for Person and WebSite schemas in layout.tsx.
  ✓ OpenGraph and Twitter card metadata fully configured.
  ✓ metadataBase set — relative OG image URLs resolve correctly.
  ✓ Canonical URL set to "/".
  ✓ Vercel deployment configuration present (vercel.json).
  ✓ CI workflow (ci.yml) runs lint and build on push to master and PRs.
  ✓ NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL validated at runtime with a dev fallback.

Findings:

  [MED] F-BUILD-01: vercel.json uses pnpm for install/build but CI uses
    pnpm and README implies npm. See F-DEP-02. The Vercel deployment should
    be consistent with CI.

  [MED] F-BUILD-02: og-image.png is referenced in metadata but the file
    may not be optimized. The image is a static asset in public/ — it will
    be served as-is. Confirm the file exists, is 1200×630, and is <200 KB.
    Social media crawlers may timeout on large OG images.

  [LOW] F-BUILD-03: CI workflow triggers only on master branch.
    Feature branches and PRs targeting master are covered, but no scheduled
    build runs exist to detect dependency drift over time. Consider adding
    a weekly scheduled workflow.

  [LOW] F-BUILD-04: No lighthouse or performance budget CI step.
    Core Web Vitals are not measured in CI. Adding a Lighthouse CI step
    (even as advisory) would catch regressions before release.

  [LOW] F-BUILD-05: ANALYZE=true next build is available but undocumented
    in README. Add a note so contributors know to use it when adding
    large dependencies.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  11. VISUAL IDENTITY & POLISH
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SCORE: 6/10

Strengths:
  ✓ Dark-first aesthetic with a clear, consistent color palette.
  ✓ Geist Sans + Geist Mono — modern, legible, professionally associated with
    Vercel's design language.
  ✓ Subtle radial gradient in LandingBackground adds depth without distraction.
  ✓ Accent color (#5b9cf6, blue) used consistently for interactive states.
  ✓ Responsive typography scale (h1 scales from 5xl to 4xl on mobile).
  ✓ Footer is clean: social links with aria-labeled SVG icons, copyright note.
  ✓ EntryTrigger breathing animation adds subtle life to the landing stage.

Findings:

  [HIGH] F-VIS-01: Lottie placeholder animation is not a brand asset.
    Both the IdentityBlock avatar and LandingVisualLayer background use
    placeholder.json. This is a generic placeholder, not a personal or
    brand-specific animation. The most visible element of the landing page
    needs to be replaced with intentional visual design before v1.
    Action: Design or source:
      a) A personal avatar animation or stylized initials for IdentityBlock.
      b) An atmospheric / particle animation for the background layer.

  [MED] F-VIS-02: No logo or wordmark.
    The site has no visual logo — only text. For a portfolio focused on
    craft and attention to detail, a simple SVG monogram or wordmark would
    significantly elevate first impression.

  [MED] F-VIS-03: og-image.png is present in public/ but was not visually
    inspected. The OG image is the first visual impression on social shares.
    Ensure it matches the site's dark aesthetic and includes name + tagline.

  [LOW] F-VIS-04: favicon.ico is the default Next.js favicon.
    The browser tab icon should reflect the personal brand, not a generic
    Next.js icon. Replace with a custom favicon (SVG preferred for modern
    browsers; add to app/ as favicon.ico and icon.svg).

  [LOW] F-VIS-05: No light/dark mode toggle.
    The site is dark-only. Some users prefer light mode. Even a simple
    system-preference-respect via prefers-color-scheme would improve reach.
    This is deferred from v1 per current theme strategy.

  [LOW] F-VIS-06: Accent color (#5b9cf6) is a standard blue.
    Consider a more distinctive accent that reflects personal identity.
    This is a design decision, not a code issue.

